The '''Israel Meteorological Service''' ({{lang-he|השירות המטאורולוגי הישראלי}}, ''HaSherut HaMete'orologi HaYisra'eli'') is a unit of the Israeli Ministry of Transportation that is responsible for forecasting weather, meteorological data supply and climate research in Israel. Its origins begin in 1930's in a meteorological unit established by the [[Mandatory Palestine|British Mandate]] government mainly as a support to the evolving aviation needs at the time. After establishment of the state of Israel, it was incorporated into the newly established ministry of transport. It is a member of the [[World Meteorological Organization]] since 1949. the Israeli Meteorological Service runs more than 150 measuring stations across Israel. Located between [[Rishon LeZion]], [[Mishmar HaShiva]], and [[Holon]], it is traditionally identified with also nearby [[Beit Dagan]].
